==Drops==
''In addition to the 100% drop, the player will also have two rolls on the Alchemical Hydra's drop table. The first drop has a chance to be a unique, while the second is always standard. The drop rates in the drop table below reflect the chance of getting an item for every roll on the standard loot table. For example, a listed drop rate of 2/100 indicates that you have two 2/100 chances of receiving that item.''{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1084600369995571203|date=13 January 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/jvzU5|archivedate=16 April 2019|quote=The first roll will go to the unique table OR to the standard table. The second roll will always go to the standard table. And you only get one pet roll in either situation.}}

''Drops remain on the ground for 3 hours, or until the player leaves the instanced area.''{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1688468997375762432|date=7 August 2023|archiveurl=https://archive.is/722cp|archivedate=10 August 2023|quote=I believe those are 180 mins. This is not universal across all instances, but it's been enabled for quite a few repeatable boss rooms.}}

